<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 01:17:32 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>Starcloud获1.7亿美元A轮融资，用于建设太空数据中心</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/starcloud-raises-170-million-series-a-to-build-data-centers-in-space</link><description>Starcloud 成为最快达到独角兽地位的 Y Combinator 初创公司，距演示日仅 17 个月。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/starcloud-raises-170-million-series-a-to-build-data-centers-in-space3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 01:17:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/starcloud-raises-170-million-series-a-to-build-data-centers-in-space</guid></item><item><title>几十年后脑部疾病？研究将儿童手术与淀粉样蛋白的积累联系起来</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/brain-disease-decades-later-study-links-childhood-surgery-to-amyloid-build-up</link><description>一份新报告描述了两名异常年轻的患者，他们在儿童心脏手术几十年后出现了脑淀粉样血管病。研究人员怀疑β淀粉样蛋白可能是通过当时使用的尸体手术材料无意中传播的。这一发现并不意味着阿尔茨海默病在日常生活中具有传染性，但它确实增加了证据，表明过去罕见的医疗暴露可能会在数年后导致异常的大脑蛋白质积累。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-disease-decades-later-study-links-childhood-surgery-to-amyloid-build-up.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 01:02:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/brain-disease-decades-later-study-links-childhood-surgery-to-amyloid-build-up</guid></item><item><title>气溶胶喷射印刷为下一代技术创造耐用、低功耗的晶体管</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/aerosol-jet-printing-creates-durable-low-power-transistors-for-next-generation-tech</link><description>得益于美国能源部 (DOE) 阿贡国家实验室科学家的最新研究，被称为微电子学的微型电子设备有一天可能会像纸上的文字一样容易地被打印出来。基于印刷电子领域多年的进步，该团队展示了如何通过结合定制墨水和专门的印刷工艺来创建耐用、低功耗的电子开关（称为晶体管）。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/aerosol-jet-printing-creates-durable-low-power-transistors-for-next-generation-tech.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 00:47:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/aerosol-jet-printing-creates-durable-low-power-transistors-for-next-generation-tech</guid></item><item><title>天体物理学家追踪太空中贵重金属的起源，从碰撞的恒星到合并的星系</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/astrophysicists-trace-the-origin-of-valuable-metals-in-space-from-colliding-stars-to-merging-galaxies</link><description>在数十亿光年之外的宇宙偏远地区，两颗中子星（死亡恒星的超致密残余物）相撞。这次灾难性的宇宙事件发出了光和粒子，包括伽马射线的突然闪光，流过宇宙。这些伽马射线在到达地球之前传播了 85 亿年。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/astrophysicists-trace-the-origin-of-valuable-metals-in-space-from-colliding-stars-to-merging-galaxies.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 00:32:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/astrophysicists-trace-the-origin-of-valuable-metals-in-space-from-colliding-stars-to-merging-galaxies</guid></item><item><title>全基因组精细作图提高了因果变异的识别</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/genome-wide-fine-mapping-improves-identification-of-causal-variants</link><description>一种利用功能注释进行全基因组精细作图的新方法在多个指标上优于当前方法，包括误差控制、作图能力、分辨率、精度、复制率和跨祖先表型预测。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/genome-wide-fine-mapping-improves-identification-of-causal-variants.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 00:17:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/genome-wide-fine-mapping-improves-identification-of-causal-variants</guid></item><item><title>出生时非亲属的合作巩固了抹香鲸的社会复杂性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cooperation-by-non-kin-during-birth-underpins-sperm-whale-social-complexity</link><description>在一项前所未有的观察中，研究人员&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cooperation-by-non-kin-during-birth-underpins-sperm-whale-social-complexity2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 00:02:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cooperation-by-non-kin-during-birth-underpins-sperm-whale-social-complexity</guid></item><item><title>新发现的隐性神经发育障碍可能是有史以来最普遍的</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/newly-discovered-recessive-neurodevelopmental-disorder-may-be-most-prevalent-ever</link><description>纽约西奈山伊坎医学院的研究人员发现并描述了一种以前未知的隐性神经发育障碍（NDD），它似乎是迄今为止发现的最普遍的疾病。这种情况是由称为 RNU2-2 的小非编码基因的变化引起的。据估计，它会影响美国数千人，约占所有已知遗传原因的隐性 NDD 病例的 10%。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/newly-discovered-recessive-neurodevelopmental-disorder-may-be-most-prevalent-ever.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 23:47:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/newly-discovered-recessive-neurodevelopmental-disorder-may-be-most-prevalent-ever</guid></item><item><title>Eyal Aharoni——打破道德图灵测试</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/eyal-aharoni-breaking-the-moral-turing-test</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 23:32:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/eyal-aharoni-breaking-the-moral-turing-test</guid></item><item><title>Aubrey de Gray — 我们距离老鼠的强劲复兴还有多远？为什么这很重要？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/aubrey-de-grey-how-close-are-we-to-robust-mouse-rejuvenation-and-why-does-that-matter</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 23:17:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/aubrey-de-grey-how-close-are-we-to-robust-mouse-rejuvenation-and-why-does-that-matter</guid></item><item><title>超级奇怪”——神经科学家发现成人大脑充满了数百万个“沉默的突触”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/super-bizarre-neuroscientists-discover-that-adult-brain-is-filled-with-millions-of-silent-synapses</link><description>科学家们在成人大脑中发现了数量惊人的“沉默突触”——未使用的神经连接，可以快速激活以存储新的记忆。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/super-bizarre-neuroscientists-discover-that-adult-brain-is-filled-with-millions-of-silent-synapses.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 23:02:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/super-bizarre-neuroscientists-discover-that-adult-brain-is-filled-with-millions-of-silent-synapses</guid></item></channel></rss>